  "id": "laboni-akter",
  "name": "Laboni Akter",
  "title": "Senior Lecturer",
  "department": "Bangla Language & Literature (BLL)",
  "school": "",
  "profile_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/faculty/laboni-akter",
  "photo_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/sites/default/files/styles/faculty_avatar/public/images/faculty/Laboni-Akter-300.jpg?itok=EW8MmuhJ",
  "bio_raw": "Laboni Akter (alias Laboni Ashrafi) is a Senior Lecturer in the Department of Bengali Language & Literature at the University of Liberal Arts Bangladesh. She holds an MA and BA in Bangla Language & Literature from the University of Dhaka and a PGD in Filmmaking from Bangladesh Cinema & Television Institute.\nAn emerging academician and creative professional, Akter has produced, written, and directed award-winning films and received research fellowships. Her research interests encompass Cinema Studies, Cinematic Realism, Gender Politics, Indigenous Studies, Diaspora Studies, and Ecofeminism. Akter has authored two books and several articles on Feminist Film Theory, South Asian Cinema, and Ethnic Language & Literature.\nShe is currently investigating the role of matrilineal society in preserving indigenous culture among the Garo community in Bangladesh, funded by the Ministry of Cultural Affairs. Her work on indigenous studies and medieval studies has been invited to the IAHR conference in Poland and Medieval Congress in London. Akter is the convenor of the 1st BLL Students' Conference at ULAB, focusing on interdisciplinary socio-cultural studies.\nDescribing herself as a 'visual poet', Akter's films explore the social and psychological conditions of women. A feminist and women's rights advocate, she uses her filmmaking to examine women's societal status, rights, and challenges to their emancipation.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "Film & Media Studies, Gender Politics, Indigenous Studies, Cultural Studies, Ecofeminism."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nPGD, Filmmaking (Screenplay Writing & Direction)\n, Bangladesh Cinema & Television Institute (BCTI)\nMA, Bangla\n, University of Dhaka\nBA, Bangla\n, University of Dhaka"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journal Articles\n“Exploring Epic Form in Cinema: A Linguistic Analysis of ‘Chandrabati Katha’” [Bengali]. Bangladesh Cinema & Television Institute Journal, No. 14. (December 2025).\n“Subaltern Narratives in Bhanubil: A Critical Analysis of Colonial Exploitation, Resistance, and Identity” [Bengali].\nTrisangam International Refereed Journal\n, Volume: V, Issue: V. ISSN: 2583-0848. (October 2025).\n“Women's life and world in the films of Bangladeshi women filmmakers” [Bengali].\nBangladesh Cinema & Television Institute Journal\n, No. 12. (June 2023).\n“Did Satyajit fall in love with Kanchenjunga?” [Bengali].\nProthom Alo\n. (May 2023).\nhttps://www.prothomalo.com/onnoalo/fawik4nw0n\n“The grey world of Kiarostami and Jibanananda” [Bengali].\nIrabotee\n, Festival Edition: Cinema. (October 2021).\nhttps://irabotee.com/puja-2021-film-article-laboni-ashrafi/\n“‘Human civilization moves forward by drinking mother's blood’ — Mother archetype and mythological rebel women in Ritwik's films” [Bengali].\nIrabotee\n. (June 2020).\n“Robert Bresson and his films” [Bengali].\nTeerandaz\n, Festival Edition (2020).\n‘This is the way the light shines, this is the way the world will be free’ – Cinema and some words” [Bengali].\nAkaalbodhon\n, Cinema Edition, Sub Editorial. (21 June 2020).\n“Memoir: Mohiuddin Faroque” [Bengali].\nAkaalbodhon\n, Cinema Edition. (21 June 2020).",
